Aquarius, Gold Fields, Standard Bank: South African Equity Market Preview

-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 
2011-08-10T22:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/gold-fields-standard-bank-south-african-stock-market-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parenthesis and prices are
from the close of trade.  The FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index snapped five days of
declines, adding 0.9 percent to 28,658.57 in Johannesburg
yesterday.  Aquarius Platinum Ltd. (AQP)  : The company releases
earnings for the year through June. The shares surged 9 percent
to 27.59 rand.  Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI SJ): Africa’s second-biggest producer
of the metal releases first-half earnings. The stock rallied 6.5
percent to 112.50 rand.  Standard Bank  Group Ltd. (SBK SJ): the continent’s biggest
lender reports first-half earnings. The shares gained 0.2
percent to 90.50 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mike Cohen in  Cape Town  at 
 mcohen21@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 